verbose_text: Although RAG is found throughout euchromatic regions of the nucleus (XREF_FIG) and is bound genome wide to H3K4me3 enriched sites, we know that RAG cleavage is inherently inefficient because breaks are detected on target loci in approximately 20% or less of cells.
